---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Modern Static Sites with Astro" description="A guide to modern static site generators and automated deployment.">
    <header class="text-center mb-10">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800">Modern Static Sites & Deployment</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-600">Exploring modern tools and reusable patterns for publishing content on the web.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-rocket text-orange-500 mr-2"></i>Astro with GitHub Pages</h2>
            <p>Astro is a modern static site generator built for performance and flexibility. This entire site is built with it.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 mt-2">
                <li>Install Astro: <code>npm create astro@latest</code></li>
                <li>Develop locally: <code>npm run dev</code></li>
                <li>Build your static site: <code>npm run build</code></li>
                <li>Deploy with the official Astro GitHub Actions workflow.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-gem text-red-500 mr-2"></i>Jekyll with GitHub Pages</h2>
            <p>Jekyll is the original static site generator with native support on GitHub Pages.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm border">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-bolt text-green-500 mr-2"></i>Hugo</h2>
            <p>Hugo is known for its incredible speed, as it's built with the Go programming language.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-blue-800"><i class="fa-solid fa-recycle mr-2"></i>The Reusable Pattern</h2>
            <p>Every setup shares this core pattern: write content in simple formats (like Markdown), use templates to control structure, and automate builds with CI/CD tools like GitHub Actions to host for free on GitHub Pages.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
